{{Orphan|date=December 2010}}

'''Balleny Trough''' ({{Coord|66|S|158|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea trough named in association with the [[Balleny Islands]]. The name was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in February 1972.

==References==
* {{usgs-gazetteer|id=17178}}

[[Category:Oceanic basins of the Southern Ocean]]


{{marine-geo-stub}}

{{Orphan|date=April 2011}}

'''Byrd Canyon''' ({{Coord|75|30|S|157|15|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea canyon named for Admiral [[Richard E. Byrd]]. The name was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in June 1988.

==References==
* {{usgs-gazetteer|id=17168}}

