{{Other uses|Grass Valley (disambiguation){{!}}Grass Valley}}
{{unreferenced|date=January 2015}}
A '''grass valley''' (also '''vega''' and '''valle''') is a [[meadow]] located within a [[forest|forested]] and relatively small [[drainage basin]] such as  a [[headwater]].  Grass valleys are common in [[North America]], where they are created and maintained principally by the work of [[beaver]]s.  Rarely, they are associated with [[cienega]]s.

The words vega and valle are [[loanword]]s from [[Spanish language|Spanish]].

==Notable examples==
*[[Valles Caldera]], New Mexico
*[[Las Vegas Springs Preserve]], Nevada

